## 12. Toast / Alert

### Purpose
A transient notification that communicates the result of a system action ŌĆö a successful save, a validation warning, a destructive error, an informational update. Toasts appear briefly and dismiss automatically or on user action.

### Layout Composition
Toasts are positioned `fixed bottom-6 right-6 z-50` (or in a toast stack container). Each toast is `flex items-start gap-3 w-full max-w-sm p-4`. It contains a status icon (20├Ś20), a text block (title + description in `flex flex-col gap-1`), and an optional dismiss button (`X`, ghost, icon-sm) on the right.

### Token Assembly (info variant ŌĆö base)

| Part | Property | Token | Tailwind class |
