## 5. Border Radius

| Token | Value | Usage |
|---|---|---|
| `radius-none` | `0px` | Flat elements ŌĆö images, hero sections |
| `radius-sm` | `2px` | **Default** ŌĆö inputs, buttons, badges, cards |
| `radius-md` | `4px` | Slightly softer ŌĆö dropdowns, tooltips |
| `radius-lg` | `6px` | Panels, modals |
| `radius-xl` | `8px` | Large cards, sheets (use sparingly) |
| `radius-full` | `9999px` | Avatars only ŌĆö everything else stays sharp |

**Default component radius:** `radius-sm` (`2px`). The sharp directive means almost no rounding. Elements should feel cut, not moulded. Only avatars use `radius-full`.

